qcl
------------------------------------------
Despite many common concepts with classical computer science, quantum
computing is still widely considered as a special discipline within the broad
field of theoretical physics. One reason for the slow adoption of QC by the
computer science community is the confusing variety of formalisms (Dirac
notation, matrices, gates, operators, etc.), none of which has any similarity
with classical programming languages, as well as the rather physical
terminology in most of the available literature.

QCL (Quantum Computation Language) tries to fill this gap: QCL is a high
level, architecture independent programming language for quantum computers,
with a syntax derived from classical procedural languages like C or Pascal.
This allows for the complete implementation and simulation of quantum
algorithms (including classical components) in one consistent formalism.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.4-1
  libgcc1-4.9.3-1
  libplotter2-2.6-4
  libreadline7-6.3.8-1
  libstdc++6-4.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.3-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://tph.tuwien.ac.at/~oemer/qcl.html

Canonical download:
  http://tph.tuwien.ac.at/~oemer/tgz/qcl-0.6.4.tgz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack qcl-0.6.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./qcl-0.6.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/qcl-0.6.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/qcl-0.6.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(qcl)
  /usr/bin/qcl.exe
  /usr/lib/qcl/default.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/deutsch.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/dft.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/examples.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/grover.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/linalg.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/modarith.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/primes.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/shor.qcl
  /usr/lib/qcl/test.qcl
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/qcl.README
  /usr/share/doc/qcl/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/qcl/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/qcl/README

